-- Rookie Marquez, 20, Becomes Youngest-Ever MotoGP World Champion
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-11-10T15:09:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-10/rookie-marquez-20-becomes-youngest-ever-motogp-world-champion.html
Rookie motorcycle racer Marc Marquez
became the youngest-ever winner of the world MotoGP championship
after coming third in today’s Valencia Grand Prix.  Honda rider Marquez, a 20-year-old Spaniard, clinched the
title on home soil in the last race of the 18-event season.
Spain’s Jorge Lorenzo of Yamaha, twice world champion, won
today’s race, with compatriot Dani Pedrosa of Honda second.  Marquez had previously failed to wrap up the title at races
in Australia and Japan.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 